node.text:
Does it ever feel like there aren’t enough hours in a day to accomplish everything you hope to accomplish? 

While balancing work and life in a 24-hour period can be a tricky act, there are simple steps you can take to make your daily routine more manageable in order to achieve more in the short term and long term. Join @dorieclark, an industry expert, author, and speaker, for this webinar to hear her insights into how to make the most of your day, every day. Hosted by @itsterryrice. Link in bio to register.

node.title: Webinar: How To Make The Most Out Your 24 Hours

node.text: "Used-to-be’s don't make no honey. So don't nobody care what you used to be!" — artist, TV personality, and founder @kandi tells Entrepreneur's @heyfeifer the philosophy that keeps her going. Don't rest when things go well. Don't give up when things go badly. No matter what, just keep moving!

node.text:
Entrepreneur's @heyfeifer chats with Chef @priavanda, head chef and owner of NYC-restaurant @desigalli, about how she kept her restaurant open and launch two new businesses during lockdown.

PriaVanda is also featured at the Boost with Facebook Good Ideas Festival, a virtual celebration of small businesses. The Festival will offer inspiration and education for small businesses all over the world. You can learn more about it at Fb.com/goodideasfestival.

node.text:
We have all learned during the pandemic that anything can happen. So how can entrepreneurs stay alert — and stay ahead — of future problems big and small?

@nicolewalters, CEO and founder of @inheritlearning, chats with @travis.montaque, CEO and founder of @holler.io, about staying flexible and adapting to new opportunities. (Brought to you by @delltech)

node.title: Succeed by Staying Flexible in Business

node.text: On this week's episode of #habitsandhustle with @therealjencohen, professional boxer and MMA athlete @claressashields talks about mindset, routine, and the challenges she’s faced to get to where she is. Listen to the full episode on Apple Podcasts.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The Top 5 Challenges of Being an Entrepreneur (and How to Overcome Them) Entrepreneur'.

node.text:
Entrepreneurship is difficult, but it's worth it. 

(Full article by @high.deepak in our link in bio.)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The Top 5 Challenges of Being an Entrepreneur (and How to Overcome Them) Entrepreneur'.

Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CHALLENGE I Doubt Myself SOLUTION Look to fellow entrepreneurs for inspiration. Read their books, listen to their podcasts, and follow their social accounts. If they can succeed, so can you! Entrepreneur'.

Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CHALLENGE I Get Overwhelmed Managing Large Projects SOLUTION Set up realistic expectations for what you need to succeed going into this venture! You may have to work weekends and late nights, but no successful business is built without some sacrifices. Entrepreneur'.

Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CHALLENGE I Don't Know How to Build a Strong Team SOLUTION Set high goals for yourself and figure out the impact you want your business to have on the world. A purpose-driven business attracts an A-team. Entrepreneur'.

Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CHALLENGE I Struggle to Manage Close Relationships SOLUTION Find a romantic partner who is fully supportive of your venture, or stay stay single until you are confident that you have established a business that you can lean on in the future. Entrepreneur'.

Photo by Entrepreneur on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CHALLENGE I Worry About Managing Cashflow & Finances SOLUTION Have patience and learn from your experiences. This may seem like a cop out but you need to develop your gut instincts in order to successfully manage capital, cash flow, and manpower at the early stages of a business. Entrepreneur'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneur on September 07, 2021 tagging @meetcute. May be an image of 1 person, sitting and text that says 'UNTIL "IT DIDN'T DAWN ON ME LATER THAT THE CHARACTERS IN ROMANTIC COMEDIES ALL LOOKED THE SAME. AND THEY DIDN'T LOOK LIKE ME." NAOMI SHAH'.

node.text: “Something I love to think about is that there are meet-cutes happening millions of times a day,” says Naomi Shah. “That’s eight billion rom-coms to tell.” Shah is the founder of @meetcute, a modern rom-com studio that tells stories through 15-minute podcasts, and so far its 300 podcast episodes have been listened to more than two million times. With $9.25 million in funding, Shah is making Meet Cute a go-to source for millennial and Gen Z listeners looking for inclusive, diverse, creative stories. Read more about her journey in the link in bio.

node.text:
Does it ever feel like there aren’t enough hours in a day to accomplish everything you hope to accomplish? 

While balancing work and life in a 24-hour period can be a tricky act, there are simple steps you can take to make your daily routine more manageable in order to achieve more in the short term and long term. Join @dorieclark, an industry expert, author, and speaker, for this webinar to hear her insights into how to make the most of your day, every day. Hosted by @itsterryrice. Link in bio to register.

node.text: "When I had a year and a half off from the game, I took a few courses at Harvard Business School and was never so intimidated in my life," says tennis star @mariasharapova. "I was intimidated to raise my hand and ask a question, because I didn’t know a lot of the answers. But once I got comfortable not being the smartest one in the room, the fact that I was learning and growing was so fulfilling." Read more about what losing has taught Sharapova about winning, link in bio.
